-- Lagardere Sells Russian Radio Business for $162 Million
-- B y   C a r o l   M a t l a c k
-- 2011-12-23T18:26:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-23/lagardere-sells-russian-radio-business-for-162-million.html
Lagardere SCA (MMB)  sold its Russian radio
business, Europa Media Group, to a group of private Russian
investors for $162 million, the company said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Europa Media Group generated revenue of 43 million euros
($56 million) in 2010, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carol Matlack in Paris at 
